                <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 812.512/318.</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">Special Agent <persName type="from">Canova</persName> to the
                            <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>.</hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram.]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Saltillo</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1914-07-04">
                            <hi rend="italic">July 4, 1914</hi>
                        </date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>In regard to the Department’s June 26, 5 p.m., referred to me, Villareal,
                    Secretary of the Treasury, has directed port authorities Tampico to accept New
                    York exchange at the prevailing gold rates and to facilitate movement of
                    shipping in every manner.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Canova</hi>
                    </signed>.</closer>
            </div>
        </body>
